This is a bug.  Per [\[cmath.syn\]][1] `sqrtl` is a member of the `std` namespace.  

&gt;     namespace std {
		  [...]
		  float sqrt(float x);  // see [library.c]
		  double sqrt(double x);
		  long double sqrt(long double x);  // see [library.c]
		  float sqrtf(float x);
		  long double sqrtl(long double x);
		  [...]
    }

This is legal code and will compile in [MSVS][2] and [Clang][3].

There is a [bug report for this in GCC][4] but it has not yet been taken care of since it is very trivial and their resources are finite.


